main event: An unidentified object observed in the sky near Mannasquam, New Jersey, exhibiting a pronounced vapor-trail and traveling at a high speed on October 6, 1957.
interesting points: The object was estimated to be very high in altitude and moved in several sharp turns,The sighting lasted for 1-2 minutes,The object appeared silver and was slightly smaller than the vapor trail it created,Ground observers were unable to identify the object as an aircraft due to the absence of wings,Weather conditions were clear during the observation.
sighted object: one silver object with a pronounced vapor-trail
witness description: the observer was in their driveway
